laboratory_examinations.findings: Cholelithiasis with a single 26 mm gallstone within the gallbladder. No gallbladder wall thickening or pericholecystic fluid. No intra or extrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation. Common bile duct measures up to 5 mm in diameter. Signal drop on opposed phase gradient echo images consistent with hepatic steatosis with a fat fraction of 10%.
